@prefix chorus: <https://jeffbridwell.com/chorus#> .
@prefix rdfs:   <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

# #3545 — shape-valid Products. comment emitted as BOTH rdfs:comment (shape sh:path) AND chorus:comment (generator field projection) — dual until the generator aligns. From products.json.
# #3603 — this file is THE definition home for child products (ProductShape floor
# content); structural edges (partOf / hasDomain / consumes / atStep) live in
# roles/silas/ontology/chorus.ttl. Added: product-clearing, product-spine,
# product-pulse, product-convergence (roster per Jeff 2026-07-03: Chorus →
# {Athena, Loom, Werk, Borg, Clearing→{Spine, Pulse}, Convergence}; Gathering
# top-level; Senses not a product). chorusProduct / borgProduct / gathering keep
# their legacy IRIs and defs in chorus.ttl (IRI convergence is #1772).
# hasDesignDoc: unfilled everywhere, named in gaps — no Document instances exist
# in the graph (docs live in doc-catalog-registry.json); convergence follow-on.

chorus:product-athena a chorus:Product ;
    rdfs:label "Athena" ; chorus:label "Athena" ;
    rdfs:comment "Athena is the structural and query layer of Chorus — the canonical model of what exists in the team's product world (products, domains, services, value-streams) and the predicates that connect them." ; chorus:comment "Athena is the structural and query layer of Chorus — the canonical model of what exists in the team's product world (products, domains, services, value-streams) and the predicates that connect them." ;
    chorus:ownedBy chorus:role-wren ;
    chorus:status "building" ;
    chorus:audience "Gates, SessionStart envelope injection, blast-radius, role-nudge routing, demo feedback, the tagging layer, and Jeff and the team via the rendered tree page." ;
    chorus:valueProposition "One queryable source of truth for the product tree with no fallback that yields a different answer, so every structural and impact question resolves to a real tree IRI rather than memory or pattern-matching." ;
    chorus:vision "A single SHACL-gated model whose one generator projects Product, Domain, Service, and ValueStream into uniform generated APIs and pages, made whole by construction through the DAL as the only write path." ;
    chorus:gaps "A v1 predicate layer still being cleaned, the Service class not yet instantiated, and the generator not yet projecting inverse-path relationships as nested fields." .

# product-borg RETIRED (#3603) — it duplicated chorus:borgProduct (the edge-holder:
# ~30 inbound partOf/belongsTo/hasDomain edges in chorus.ttl). One node per product:
# borgProduct survives; product-borg's floor content was folded onto borgProduct's
# definition in chorus.ttl. The live product-borg instance is deleted by the #3603
# migration.

chorus:product-werk a chorus:Product ;
    rdfs:label "Werk" ; chorus:label "Werk" ;
    rdfs:comment "The Chorus execution protocol that carries a unit of work from pulled to proven-and-accepted, across the Building and Proving steps." ; chorus:comment "The Chorus execution protocol that carries a unit of work from pulled to proven-and-accepted, across the Building and Proving steps." ;
    chorus:ownedBy chorus:role-kade ;
    chorus:status "operating" ;
    chorus:audience "The three roles building Chorus and Gathering plus Jeff accepting the work; the external customer never touches Werk." ;
    chorus:valueProposition "Every accepted card leaves as merged source on origin/main with a coherent receipt — one trace from pull to deployed cdhash — so a green result can't lie and work arrives proven rather than taken on faith." ;
    chorus:vision "Generated domain APIs over the graph end the reconcile treadmill structurally — typed contracts at every boundary, every card a coherent SKU." ;
    chorus:gaps "werk-test is held behind the generated tests-domain API; the tests domain lacks per-test identity and result ingestion; card-acceptance does not yet advance artifact status; advisory test and review steps are not yet gates." .

chorus:product-clearing a chorus:Product ;
    rdfs:label "The Clearing" ; chorus:label "The Clearing" ;
    rdfs:comment "Multi-party real-time alignment — browser chat with Jeff and all three AI roles. Parent product of Spine and Pulse." ; chorus:comment "Multi-party real-time alignment — browser chat with Jeff and all three AI roles. Parent product of Spine and Pulse." ;
    chorus:ownedBy chorus:role-wren ;
    chorus:status "operating" ;
    chorus:audience "Jeff and all three roles during alignment moments. Borg reads the transcripts, and decisions marked in-channel are captured to the decision log." ;
    chorus:valueProposition "Real-time multi-party alignment with decisions captured where they happen — Jeff stops being the transport layer between role terminals." ;
    chorus:vision "One shared room where the team aligns in minutes instead of relaying briefs, with every DECISION: line landing in the graph automatically." ;
    chorus:gaps "hasDesignDoc unfilled (no Document instances in graph). Transcript indexing depends on the index-freshness pipeline that alerts today." .

chorus:product-spine a chorus:Product ;
    rdfs:label "Spine" ; chorus:label "Spine" ;
    rdfs:comment "The audit trail — structured event log of all team activity and state changes. Child product of The Clearing." ; chorus:comment "The audit trail — structured event log of all team activity and state changes. Child product of The Clearing." ;
    chorus:ownedBy chorus:role-wren ;
    chorus:status "operating" ;
    chorus:audience "All roles and Borg as writers/readers, and Jeff via dashboards, traces, and readouts." ;
    chorus:valueProposition "One append-only truth about what happened — traces, fitness functions, and Borg's reflection all read the same spine instead of competing logs." ;
    chorus:vision "Every act in the system is an event on one spine with a threaded trace — the team's history is queryable, not anecdotal." ;
    chorus:gaps "hasDesignDoc unfilled (no Document instances in graph). ADR-046 spine reshape (EmitContract consumption, failureClass spans) in flight." .

chorus:product-pulse a chorus:Product ;
    rdfs:label "Pulse" ; chorus:label "Pulse" ;
    rdfs:comment "Agent vital signs — heartbeats, declared role states, andon, at-a-glance health of the running team. Child product of The Clearing." ; chorus:comment "Agent vital signs — heartbeats, declared role states, andon, at-a-glance health of the running team. Child product of The Clearing." ;
    chorus:ownedBy chorus:role-silas ;
    chorus:status "operating" ;
    chorus:audience "Jeff at a glance, the roles for mutual observation, alerting as a consumer." ;
    chorus:valueProposition "Silence becomes a signal: heartbeats and declared states let the roles watch each other, so Jeff is never the first to notice a stall." ;
    chorus:vision "The running team is legible at a glance — who is alive, building, blocked, or dark, without anyone asking." ;
    chorus:gaps "hasDesignDoc unfilled (no Document instances in graph). Nudge-delivery health (no-window failures) still alerts. Pulse domain newly authored in #3603." .

chorus:product-convergence a chorus:Product ;
    rdfs:label "Convergence" ; chorus:label "Convergence" ;
    rdfs:comment "Cross-domain integration — ICDs, harvesters, data pipelines. The product whose job is making the many sources one graph." ; chorus:comment "Cross-domain integration — ICDs, harvesters, data pipelines. The product whose job is making the many sources one graph." ;
    chorus:ownedBy chorus:role-wren ;
    chorus:status "building" ;
    chorus:audience "The roles as integration authors, the graph as the destination, the ICD gate as the enforcement point." ;
    chorus:valueProposition "Harvesters and pipelines governed by ICDs — every integration is declared before it is coded, so data lineage is a contract rather than an accident." ;
    chorus:vision "Data from every surface converges into the one graph through declared contracts; the V1/V2 domain-layer convergence is this product finishing its own job." ;
    chorus:gaps "hasDesignDoc unfilled (no Document instances in graph). V1/V2 domain IRI duplication outstanding. Change-management engine (impact, propagate, verify) not yet built." .

chorus:product-loom a chorus:Product ;
    rdfs:label "Loom" ; chorus:label "Loom" ;
    rdfs:comment "The operating-model and team-knowledge layer of Chorus — the team's persistent product memory at the Shaping step — carrying principles, practices, policies, decisions, roles, skills, and RCAs." ; chorus:comment "The operating-model and team-knowledge layer of Chorus — the team's persistent product memory at the Shaping step — carrying principles, practices, policies, decisions, roles, skills, and RCAs." ;
    chorus:ownedBy chorus:role-jeff ;
    chorus:status "exploring" ;
    chorus:audience "The Chorus team — the three AI roles and Jeff — for whom Loom holds the persistent normative substrate; owned by Jeff at the Shaping step." ;
    chorus:valueProposition "Loom gives the team one coherent, validated home for its normative substrate as real OWL classes with SHACL shapes, so the operating model is graphed and constrained rather than scattered as ungraphed markdown." ;
    chorus:vision "A coherent product modeled on the recursive Athena model, one clean predicate set, every content type a real OWL class with a SHACL shape, every subdomain populated or explicitly planned — Loom as the template the other products follow." ;
    chorus:gaps "5 of 7 intent subdomains are empty shells (decisions live as ungraphed markdown; Decision and RCA aren't OWL classes); the predicate layer needs cleaning; content is unconstrained by SHACL." .
